<h1 style="font-family: Helvetica Neue, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 20px; margin: 0px 0px 10px 0px; color: #fe8707; padding: 0px 20px 10px 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
	Tax Information Validation Results</h1>

<div style="width: 520px; padding: 20px 20px 20px 20px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Arial, sans-serif; color: #444; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;">
<p style="margin: 20px 0px 20px 0px">
	Hello ${toUser.firstName},<br/>
	<br/>
	The result of the I.R.S. validation of the Tax Identification Number you provided on $date.format('EEE, d MMM yyyy', $template.entity.signedOn) was
	#if(${template.entity.status.code} == 'approved')
		successfully matched with the I.R.S Tax Information Number database.
	#else
		not matched with the I.R.S Tax Information Number database.

		<p>
			The result indicates that the Tax Information Number
			#if(${template.entity.status.code} == 'invalid_tin_format' || ${template.entity.status.code} == 'invalid_request')
				is not a valid TIN.
			#elseif(${template.entity.status.code} == 'not_issued')
				provided is not currently issued.
			#elseif(${template.entity.status.code} == 'not_matched')
				and Name combination does not match with the I.R.S. records.
			#elseif(${template.entity.status.code} == 'duplicate_tin')
				already exists in the WorkMarket system.
			#elseif(${template.entity.status.code} == 'wrong_type_ssn' ||
				${template.entity.status.code} == 'wrong_type_ein' ||
				${template.entity.status.code} == 'wrong_type_both')
				and Name combination were not found in the I.R.S. records.
			#end
			Please update your W-9 from in your WorkMarket account with the correct information.
			<a href="${baseurl}/account/tax">Edit Your Tax Information</a>
		</p>

		<p style="font-weight:bold">Please note that you will not be able to withdraw funds from WorkMarket until your tax information
			has been verified with the I.R.S.</p>
	#end
	<br/>
	<p>Best Regards, <br/> WorkMarket</p>
	</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>

#parse("template/email/partials/do-not-reply.vm")